        "label": "Mercure hub JWT for publisher/subscriber authorization",
        "setup": "For a self-hosted hub, generate your own shared secret or key pair and configure it in the hub with `publisher_jwt` / `subscriber_jwt` or the `MERCURE_PUBLISHER_JWT_KEY` / `MERCURE_SUBSCRIBER_JWT_KEY` settings described in [Hub configuration](https://mercure.rocks/docs/hub/config). Then mint JWTs for publishers and/or subscribers signed with that configured key; publisher tokens must carry a `mercure.publish` claim and subscriber tokens for private updates must carry `mercure.subscribe`, as shown in [Getting Started](https://mercure.rocks/docs/getting-started) and [Troubleshooting](https://mercure.rocks/docs/hub/troubleshooting#401-unauthorized). For Mercure Cloud, buy a hub via [Pricing](https://mercure.rocks/pricing) and configure the same JWT settings from the cloud administration interface described in [Mercure Cloud](https://mercure.rocks/docs/hub/cloud).",
